{"title_page": "Matthew Knight", "text_new": "{{About|the Canadian actor|the Australian basketball player|Matthew Knight (basketball)|the stadium named for a different Matthew Knight|Matthew Knight Arena}}\n{{BLP sources|date=October 2011}}  \n{{Infobox person\n| name                  = Matthew Knight\n| image                 = \n| imagesize             = \n| caption               = \n| birth_name            = \n| birth_date            = <!-- Don't change this unless you include a reference that is not IMDb -->c. {{Birth based on age as of date|17|2011|3|15}}<ref name=YorkRegion/>\n| birth_place     Canada       = <!-- Don't change this unless you include a reference that is not IMDb  -->\n| death_date            =  \n| death_place           = \n| other_names             = \n| occupation            = Actor\n| years_active          = 2002\u20132014\n| spouse                = \n| domesticpartner       = \n| website               = \n}}\n{{External media|image1=[https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/webcitation/752be888b1e523965d2f9972ffc3f561898194ff Matthew Knight 2011<ref name=YorkRegion/>]}}\n\n'''Matthew Knight''' (born {{circa}} 1993/1994<ref name=YorkRegion/>) is a Canadian actor known for his roles in ''[[Queer as Folk (2000 TV series)|Queer as Folk]]'' and as Jake Kimble in ''[[The Grudge (film series)|The Grudge]]'' film series. Since then he has appeared in over a dozen television series, more than ten television movies and a number of feature-length and short films. He has been nominated seven times for a [[Young Artist Award]] and has won twice, for his performance in ''[[Candles on Bay Street]]'' (2006) and ''[[Gooby (film)|Gooby]]'' (2009).\n\n== Career ==\nKnight's first leading role in a feature film was Will Burton in ''Big Spender'' (2003). After performing on various television shows, he appeared in ''Peep'' (2004 and in ''[[The Greatest Game Ever Played]]'' (2005) as Young [[Francis Ouimet]]. In 2006, he appeared in the [[werewolf]] film ''[[Skinwalkers (2006 film)|Skinwalkers]]''. He later appeared in ''[[The Grudge 2]]'' (2006) and ''[[The Grudge 3]]'' (2009) as Jake Kimble.\n\nKnight later appeared ''[[The Good Witch]]'' (2008), ''[[The Good Witch's Garden]]'' (2009), ''[[The Good Witch's Gift]]'' (2010), ''[[The Good Witch's Family]]'' (2011) and \"[[The Good Witch's Charm]]\" (2012). He also starred in the television movie and series ''[[My Babysitter's a Vampire]]''. He has starred in the episodes, \"Alien Candy\" and \"Checking Out\" of the TV series, ''[[R.L. Stine's The Haunting Hour]]''.\n\n==Personal life==\nKnight resided in [[Mount Albert, Ontario]] and attended [[Unionville High School (Ontario)|Unionville High School]] where he was in the performing arts program. He has an older brother, Jack Knight, and sister, Tatum Knight, who are also actors.<ref name=YorkRegion/><ref name=Actra/>\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2004\n| ''Peep''\n| Harry\n| Short\n|-\n| 2005\n| ''[[The Greatest Game Ever Played]]''\n| Young [[Francis Ouimet]]\n|\n|-\n| 2005\n|''[[Cheaper by the Dozen 2]]''\n| Movie Theatre Kid\n|\n|-\n| 2006\n| ''[[The Grudge 2]]''\n| Jake Kimble\n|\n|-\n| 2007\n| ''[[Christmas in Wonderland]]''\n| Brian Saunders\n| \n|-\n| 2007\n| ''[[Skinwalkers (2006 film)|Skinwalkers]]''\n| Timothy Talbot\n| \n|-\n| 2008\n| ''[[Finn on the Fly]]''\n| Ben Soledad\n|\n|-\n| 2009\n| ''[[Gooby]]''\n| Willy\n| \n|-\n| 2009\n| ''[[The Grudge 3]]''\n| Jake Kimble\n|\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''Skating to New York'' \n| Jimmy Mundell\n| \n|}\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2002\n| ''[[Queer as Folk (2000 TV series)|Queer as Folk]]''\n| Peter\n| Season 2, Episode 9 : \"Accentuate the Positive\"\n|-\n| 2003\n| ''[[Missing (Canadian TV series)|1-800-Missing]]''\n| Peter Melnyk\n| Season 1, Episode 12: \"Victoria\"\n|-\n| 2003\n| ''Big Spender''\n| Will Burton\n| Television movie\n|-\n| 2005\u20132009\n| ''[[Peep and the Big Wide World]]''\n| Tom the Cat\n| Voice role\n|-\n| 2005\n| ''[[Kojak (2005 TV series)|Kojak]]''\n| Paulie Wagner\n| Season 1, Episodes 5 & 6: \"Kind of Blue\" and \"Hit Man\"\n|- \n| 2006\n| ''[[Skyland]]''\n| Spencer\n| Season 1, Episode 19: \"The Secret Power\"\n|-\n| 2006\n| ''For the Love of a Child''\n| Jacob Fletcher\n| Television movie\n|-\n| 2006\n| ''Intimate Stranger''\n| Justin Reese\n| Television movie\n|-\n| 2006\n| ''[[Candles on Bay Street]]''\n| Trooper\n| Television movie\n|-\n|-\n| 2007\n| ''All the Good Ones Are Married''\n| Luke Gold\n| Television movie\n|-\n| 2007\u20132008\n| ''[[The Dresden Files (TV series)|The Dresden Files]]''\n| Young [[Harry Dresden (TV character)|Harry Dresden]]\n| Episodes: \"What About Bob?\", \"Birds of a Feather\"\n|-\n| 2008\n| ''[[The Good Witch]]''\n| Brandon Russell\n| Television movie\n|-\n| 2009\n| ''[[The Good Witch's Garden]]''\n| Brandon Russell\n| Television movie\n|-\n| 2009\n| ''Cartoon Gene'' \n| Gene\n| Lead role\n|-\n| 2010\n| ''[[Flashpoint (TV series)|Flashpoint]]''\n| Isaac\n| Season 2, Episode 19: \"The Farm\"\n|-\n| 2010\n| ''A Heartland Christmas''\n| Sam Hawke\n| Television movie\n|-\n| 2010\n| ''[[The Good Witch's Gift]]''\n| Brandon Russell\n| Television movie\n|-\n| 2010\n| ''[[My Babysitter's a Vampire]]''\n| Ethan Morgan\n| Television movie ([[backdoor pilot]])\n|-\n| 2011\u20132012\n| ''[[My Babysitter's a Vampire (TV series)|My Babysitter's a Vampire]]''\n| Ethan Morgan\n| Main role\n|-\n| style=\"white-space: nowrap;\" | 2011, 2013\n| style=\"white-space: nowrap;\" | ''[[R.L. Stine's The Haunting Hour]]''\n| Greg / Jeremy\n| Episodes: \"Alien Candy\", \"Checking Out\"\n|-\n| 2011\n| ''[[The Good Witch's Family]]''\n| Brandon Russell\n| Television movie\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''[[The Good Witch's Charm]]''\n| Brandon Russell\n| Television movie\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''[[Magic City (TV series)|Magic City]]''\n| Big Clyd